survey_response.review_text: Dr Shalini has been a big pillar of support for us, in dealing with the niggling issues of our new born. She is very friendly and answered all all our queries, even the naive ones and took away a lot of our worries in dealing with a pre term baby. Dr. Shalini gave us a lot of tips in dealing with the new born, especially pre term with reflux issues which greatly helped us improve the feed retention and gain weight. It's only been a little over 2 weeks but Dr. Shalini already feels like the family doctor for our kid. Thank you, doctor.

Dr. Shalini is approachable and friendly.  Extremely happy with  her diagnosis and  treatment. I have been consulting her for all minor to moderate  health issues during my son’s  growing up phase.  *** ** *** **** ************** ** *****

My son was born at the hospital where Dr. Shalini practiced and she was his first pediatrician. She is friendly, patient and attentive to our queries. She is quick to allay unnecessary fears that us first time parents often conjur up and prefers to keep medications to a minimum on carefull assessment. We only moved away from her as we shifted to a new locality. Wishing you the best

With dr shalini it felt like family dr in first meeting only. Im expecting mother so lucky to have Pratima maam and Dr shalini at fortis. However dr shalini team.member Dr rishard also very coperative but dr hyder is a complete non professional and should be trained adequately that how to speak to patient and not to.misguide and should consult senior doctor before communicating desions further.
Doctor is very polite and very good examiners takes her time to diagonise step by step. Excellent doctor.

Went for treatment for our baby. The Doctor seems to be busy with phone all the time. During consultation she kept on attending calls.
No focus on treatment.
**** **** ******* Very nice attention given to babies health, most of the times diagnosis  has been very perfect and baby's health issue has been cleared soon.
The doctor took time and explained all the required details necessary. She answered all our questions and did not rush us up which is what we wanted. Good experience overall.

Most patient and friendly doctor you could have for your kid. she doesn't prescribe anything more that what is needed and very careful with her diagnosis. only wish we stayed closer to the hospital...

Dr Shalini - a very cool person yet professional. I have many doctors for inevitable reasons but I am yet come across another cool doctor as Shalini. New first time moms - you can rest assured she wouldn’t over treat your baby and she is very very patient in answering all your queries.

Dr Marie Shalini is very approachable, more so extremely patient in answering all queries. She has a knack of striking conversations with toddlers, grabbing their attention and getting them engaged. She doesn’t seem to have the practice of prescribing medicines unnecessarily.
